<table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="4"><tr bgcolor="#000000"><td><font color="#FFFFFF"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial" size="6">The Card-Killer of Loch Ness</font></td></tr></table><table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0"><tr><td></td><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Author</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Quickbeam</FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Description</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">This uses the White Arrows to pitch all your unfortunate opponent&#39;s cards.</FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Cards</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">First, some foolproof ways to win every game you ever play: <br />
#1: Simply kill your opponent. I swear, if you kill the other guy you&#39;ll win every game you ever play. <br />
#2: Corrupt your opponent&#39;s Ringbearer. THis will also ensure you a win. <br />
#3: Get to site 9 first and survive. This, I have discovered, through careful research, has proven to be the surest way of winning every game. <br />
#4: Discard all your opponent&#39;s cards from his draw deck by about site 6, then breeze on to an easy win. THis, sadly, is not such a foolproof way to victory as the previous three, but well worth  trying. However, you might not be able to pull it off if you&#39;re an idiot. A word of advice to any licensed idiots who might be reading this: DON&#39;T TRY THIS DECK!! <br />
